<paragraph blockId="23.[164,779,1819,1902]" lastBlockId="23.[826,1442,862,945]" pageId="23" pageNumber="52">Ocelli located posteriorly; posterior half of hemelytra darkened, with a subquadrangular whitish spot on apical region of corium and apex of membrane. Male generally with a larger and more globose anterior pronotal lobe, and with small spines on protibia and mesofemur.</paragraph>
